    <title>The Variety of Polar Simplices</title>
    <summary>  A collection of n distinct hyperplanes L_i ={l_i=0} in P^{n-1}, the
n-1-dimensional projective space over an algebraically closed field of
characteristic not equal to 2, is a polar simplex of a quadric Q={q=0}, if each
L_i is the polar hyperplane of the point p_i, the intersection point of the L_j
with j different from i, equivalently, if q= l_1^2+...+l_n^2 for suitable
choices of the linear forms l_i. In this paper we study the closure VPS(Q,n) in
Hilb_n(P^{n-1}) of the variety of sums of powers presenting Q from a global
viewpoint: VPS(Q,n) is a smooth Fano variety of index 2 and Picard number 1
when n&lt;6, and VPS(Q,n) is singular when n&gt;= 6.
</summary>
